# @chickadee/process-loopback has no npm-registry download to fall back on (it's
# a first-party native module) — its compiled JS wrapper and prebuilt Windows
# binary must be committed so a fresh clone works without a C++ toolchain.
!packages/process-loopback/dist/
!packages/process-loopback/prebuilds/

